Let's denote the projection of $\begin{pmatrix} -8 \\ b \end{pmatrix}$ onto $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ as p. The magnitude of the projection can be found as p=1/5(a·x), where a is the vector $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$, x is the vector $\begin{pmatrix} -8 \\ b \end{pmatrix}$, and the denominator is the magnitude of x squared, i.e., 2^2+1^2. Then |p|=(1/5)*(-8*2+b) = 2+b;
Additionally, we know that from the question we had multipling p and x gives $-8/5=-\frac{13}{5}*2$;
Combining all of these, we get b = 11/5. </think> <answer> 11/5 </answer>

